This paper deals with the visualization of complex networks and their dynamics, which is a topic that can be approached from various sub-fields of computer science. However, given the focus on social networks and the analysis of spreading phenomena, the most likely category is cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). Other relevant categories include cs.SD (Software Engineering), cs.SY (Systems and Control), cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), and cs.GR (Graphics).
